One of the most dominant languages in Tshwane (Pretoria) is not on the list of our official 11. It's been coined SePitori because it's neither Setswana, nor Sepedi nor Sesotho but is a sort of mix of all three and some other taals thrown into it. If you've never been there and are fluent in any other language, you'll probably need a bit of a crash-course so you can grasp what Pretorians are saying. We think some of these terms need to be added to the Urban Dictionary as soon as possible. Before that happens though, people on Twitter have started a trend called #LearnPitori and if you go through some of these terms then maybe, just maybe, you won't be too lost in the capital city. It's so hectic even some of us in the office from Tshwane learnt something new.  English: can i please pass..Setswana: kgopela go fetaSpitori: geo tletse pleke ore re fete kae?#LearnPitori English: they are fightingSePitori: ba ghosta#learnpitori #learnpitoriEnglish: you really good with Mathematics.Sepitori:o masepa ka Maths. English:A Group of peoplePitori:GugurancheğŸ˜ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜†#LearnPitori English: "leave me alone"Sipitori: "mfologe"#LearnPitori ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ English : How are you? Pitori: Otherwise? #learnpitori English: You tried your bestSetswana: O zamile waitsiPitori: We lwele                    ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ #learnpitori Whites: Im going to peeBotswana: Keya ntlwana boithusetsoPitori : Ko betha 6 9#Learnpitori English : I'll be back in a few minutess'Pitori: ere kere tha-the ğŸ˜‚#learnpitori Whites: I'm telling you the truthTswana: Ka nnetePitori: Mafraaaaa#LearnPitori English: Is there something wrong?Setswana: A gonale bothata?Pitori: Enden wena?ğŸ˜•#LearnPitori ğŸ˜› English: Can I please have R10Setswana: Kopa R10Pitori: Mfe jacket #LearnPitori English: We are going to call the PoliceSetswana: Rea go bitsa mapodisiSePitori: Ro bitsa van!ğŸš“#LearnPitori English: They are jealous of meSetswana: Ba njela monaSePitori: Ka ba futhumatsağŸ